{"id":40,"date":"2024-06-03T15:16:40","date_gmt":"2024-06-03T20:16:40","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/?page_id=40"},"modified":"2025-02-21T16:06:00","modified_gmt":"2025-02-21T22:06:00","slug":"report-it","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/report-it\/","title":{"rendered":"Report It"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>All members of the campus community have a duty to promptly report good faith concerns about potential hazing impacting another member of the campus community. Specifically, if any such individual holds firsthand knowledge about hazing, whether that hazing has already occurred or is set to occur in the future, they have a duty to make a reasonable effort to immediately report the hazing-related information.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <div class=\"ua_callout ua_context--info ua_layout--flow\">\n        <h2 class=\"ua_callout_title\"><span class=\"fa fa-circle-info\" title=\"Info\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/span>\n                <span class=\"ua_visually-hidden\">Info<\/span>Emergencies<\/h2>\n        \n        \n\n<p>If the situation is an emergency and you or someone else needs immediate assistance, please contact the GSU Police Department at 205-348-5454.<\/p>\n\n\n      <\/div>\n    <\/div>\n\n\n<p>To report hazing that does not involve an emergency situation, please provide specific information about the hazing incident to any of the following:<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper  \"><div class=\"ua_layout--grid\" style=--grid-column-count:2>\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\">University of Louisiana Police Department <\/h2>\n\n<p>Please call 205-348-5454. <\/p>\n\n<\/div><\/article>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\">Office of Student Conduct<\/h2>\n\n<p>Access Student Conduct&#8217;s <a href=\"https:\/\/cm.maxient.com\/reportingform.php?UnivofLouisiana&amp;layout_id=16\">online hazing report form<\/a>. Reports using this form are not anonymous.<\/p>\n\n<\/div><\/article>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\">Hazing and Harassment Hotline<\/h2>\n\n<p>Call 205-348-4258 (HALT) or fill out the <a href=\"https:\/\/secure.ethicspoint.com\/domain\/media\/en\/gui\/55675\/index.html\">hotline&#8217;s online form<\/a>. Reports to the Hazing and Harassment Hotline may be done anonymously.<\/p>\n\n<\/div><\/article>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\">Text UAct<\/h2>\n\n<p>Text 888-708-8433 (TIDE) to submit an anonymous report of hazing. Learn what to include in your report on <a href=\"https:\/\/sl.ua.edu\/anonymous-reporting-text-uact\/\">Anonymous Reporting &#8211; Text UAct<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<\/div><\/article>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n<p>The University of Louisiana\u2019s ability to effectively address incidents of hazing and enforce our Code of Student Conduct relies heavily on the accuracy and detail of the information provided. We encourage you to provide as much specific information as possible (e.g., location, dates, times, description of activity, participants, etc.) so that the University can take appropriate action in a timely manner. For reporting purposes, you have the option to complete the form below anonymously, though it could make it difficult for University officials to conduct a thorough investigation of the incident without the ability to contact the source of the report.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Making an intentionally false accusation of hazing is prohibited. Any member of the campus community who is found to have engaged in this conduct will be subject to penalties and sanctions up to and including termination from employment or suspension\/expulsion. <\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>All members of the campus community have a duty to promptly report good faith concerns about potential hazing impacting another member of the campus community. Specifically, if any such individual holds firsthand knowledge about hazing, whether that hazing has already occurred or is set to occur in the future, they have a duty to make [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"hero_blocks":"","sidebar_menu":"","sidebar":false,"sidebar_type":"select","hero":false,"title_alignment":"left","title_width":"standard","footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-40","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/40","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=40"}],"version-history":[{"count":18,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/40\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":634,"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/40\/revisions\/634"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=40"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}